node.text: When at the end of last year our storage closet at #JungalowHQ was an overflowing mess, we called in @thecontainerstore to help us get our lives for 2020! Watch and see how we transformed our storage situation with @containerstorecustomclosets #organizing #homeorganizing #organizingsolutions #organizinggoals #jungalow

node.text: We believe that good design has the power to increase the quality of life. @penandnapkinorg is a non-profit organization that shares in that belief -- their mission is to bring together families transitioning out of homelessness with designers that can help to furnish their homes. When we heard about this program, we wanted to help out. We asked our friends at @homedepot if they would be willing to provide us with all the furnishings, decorative accents, supplies, and of course planties we'd need to help make an empty house a home for this beautiful family.  Check out the full transformation here, with more on the blog! #jungalow

node.title: Home redo for a family transitioning out of homelessness 🏡♥️🌿

node.text: Jungalistas! Ever wonder, “How am I supposed to repot those cute (but spikey!) cacti friends of mine?” Us too! After quite a few prickly projects, Jungalow founder @justinablakeney, has learned about handling these pokey homies the hard way! The most important thing is to be totally prepared, so check out our video to get the tips, and then hook yourself up with one of our @bandaidbrand first aid kits to keep nearby just in case! They come free with purchase of three qualifying items at @Target! #jungalowbyebyebooboo #ad #jungalow #cacti #potitlikeitshot

node.title: How to safely repot a cactus 🌵

node.text: We have been doing these line drawings for years as a creative warm up/meditative practice. We love how the single line drawings gets us out of our heads and doesn’t allow for hesitation. If you’re in a creative rut we highly recommend trying this out. Just put pen to paper and don’t stop moving or lift off the pen until the piece feels complete! 🌸🌿✨🌷

node.text: Our Phoenix pattern is a genus of 14 species of palm trees from all over the world —This globe-trotting botanical pattern represents the connection and diversity between plants and people all over the world.
